claim.claim-text:
A detector device assisted by majority current for detecting an electromagnetic radiation (43, 46) comprising:
- a semiconductor layer (40) on which an electromagnetic radiation (43, 46) can impinge and which is doped with a dopant of a first conductivity type, the impinging electromagnetic radiation (43,46) generating pairs of majority and minority carriers in the layer (40),
- at least two control regions (MIX0, MIX1) formed in the semiconductor layer (40), being doped with a dopant of the first conductivity type;
- means (41) for generating a majority carrier current in the semiconductor layer (40) between the two control regions (MIX0, MIX1), the majority current being associated with an electrical field;
- at least two detection regions (DET0, DET1) formed in the semiconductor layer (40) and being doped with a dopant of a second conductivity type opposite to the first conductivity type, for forming a junction and collecting generated minority carriers (42), the minority carriers (42) being directed towards one of the two detection regions (DET0, DET1) under the influence of the electrical field associated with the majority carrier current;
the detector device being characterized in that:
- the detection regions (DET0, DET1) surrounds the control regions (MIX0, MIX1) for forming at least two taps,
- the concentration of dopants of the first conductivity type in the semiconductor layer (40) provides an electrical insulation between the detection regions (DET0, DET1) for avoiding leakage of minority carriers.

A detector device assisted by majority current for detecting an electromagnetic radiation (43, 46) comprising:
- a semiconductor layer (40) on which an electromagnetic radiation (43, 46) can impinge for generating pairs of majority and minority carriers therein and which is doped with a dopant of a first conductivity type,
- at least two control regions (MIX0, MIX1) formed in the semiconductor layer (40), being doped with a dopant of the first conductivity type;
- a source (41) for generating a majority carrier current in the semiconductor layer (40) between the two control regions (MIX0, MIX1), the majority current being associated with an electrical field;
- at least two detection regions (DETO, DET1) formed in the semiconductor layer (40) and being doped with a dopant of a second conductivity type opposite to the first conductivity type, for forming a junction and collecting generated minority carriers (42), the minority carriers (42) being directed towards one of the two detection regions (DETO, DET1) under the influence of the electrical field associated with the majority carrier current;
- the detection regions (DETO, DET1) surrounds the control regions (MIX0, MIX1) for forming at least two taps,
- the concentration of dopants of the first conductivity type in the semiconductor layer (40) provides an electrical insulation between the detection regions (DETO, DET1) by avoiding leakage of minority carriers from the detection regions (DETO, DET1);
the detector device being characterized in that:
- the thickness of a semiconductor substrate (44) on which the semiconductor layer (40) is formed is configured for Back Side Illumination;
- the detector device further comprises a semiconductor region of the first conductivity type (45) formed in the semiconductor layer (40) and located between the two detection regions (DETO, DET1) for insulating the detection regions (DETO, DET1), the semiconductor region (45) being a well or a deep well and comprising pixel circuitry elements (PIXEL circuitry, 21, 22).
